<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Doomsday" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Doomsday,</orth> 1) the day of the last and universal judgment: <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.274" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 274</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.243" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 243</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.232" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 232</bibl>.<lb />2) the day of death; death: <cit><quote>d. is near: die all, die merrily,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 1, 134</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>All-Souls' day is my body's d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 5.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 1, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what less than d. is the prince's doom?</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>their stolen marriage-day was Tybalt's d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.234" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 234</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>